==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Legislator
<hw>Leg"is*la`tor</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧j"⟦icr⟧s*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>legis lator</ets>, prop., a proposer of a
law; <ets>lex</ets>, <ets>legis</ets>, law + <ets>lator</ets> a
proposer, bearer, fr. <ets>latus</ets>, used as p. p. of
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear: cf. F. <ets>l⟦eacute⟧gislateur</ets>. See
<er>Legal</er>, and <er>Tolerate</er>.]</ety> <def>A lawgiver; one who
makes laws for a state or community; a member of a legislative
body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>legislators</qex> in ancient and heroical times.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many of the <qex>legislators</qex> themselves had taken an oath of
abjuration of his Majesty's person and family.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Phillips.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Legislatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
